COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 9:16PM PT yesterday, over 3.2 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 35.1 thousand have died.

In the last day, 11 thousand new infections were reported and 149 deaths. Currently 8,196 are in the hospital and 1,010 are in the ICU. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 79.4 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 5 years and older, 89% have their 1st shot and 83.3% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 7 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~50 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children under 5.
